I put the food by the door.

02:16.019 --> 02:18.146
I'm so sorry.
I will get you something else.

02:18.254 --> 02:19.448
I'm okay.

02:19.522 --> 02:22.320
No, you're exhausted and you need
something to eat.

02:22.425 --> 02:24.256
I will go get you something, okay?
Lie down.

02:24.327 --> 02:26.761
The stuff they brought earlier
was fucking disgusting.

02:26.830 --> 02:28.195
Yes, I know it was disgusting.

02:28.298 --> 02:31.358
Could you not say fucking
around the baby, maybe just like...

02:32.101 --> 02:34.797
- Give it a week, don't you think?
- Yeah, one week.

02:34.871 --> 02:37.135
Okay, one week. All right, lie down.

02:37.207 --> 02:38.333
Okay?

02:39.809 --> 02:41.299
I'll be back in a minute, all right?

02:42.045 --> 02:44.946
Your daddy's gonna get
your mommy some fucking food.

02:45.014 --> 02:47.346
- A week.
- And he'd better fucking hurry.

02:47.450 --> 02:48.781
That's very funny.

02:48.852 --> 02:50.114
[door closes]

03:19.415 --> 03:21.679
Excuse me, do you know where--
Is there-- Okay.

03:34.731 --> 03:36.198
Erin...

03:38.568 --> 03:40.001
-Jonah.
-Hi.

03:40.069 --> 03:41.263
Hi.

03:42.105 --> 03:44.733
I... I thought you moved to Brooklyn.

03:45.441 --> 03:47.272
Yeah, no, I did. I...

03:48.011 --> 03:49.740
My mom still lives here so...

03:50.580 --> 03:54.243
I'm here with her for...
for a little while, I think.

03:57.120 --> 03:59.611
I heard you were still at the college.

03:59.722 --> 04:00.882
Yeah.

04:00.957 --> 04:03.016
- Teaching or...?
- Yeah, I'm a professor now.

04:04.027 --> 04:06.257
- That was fast.
- Yeah.

04:09.365 --> 04:11.799
I hope it's nothing too serious, is it?

04:14.203 --> 04:15.568
Yeah, you know...

04:17.373 --> 04:19.807
It's tough, she's not even 60.

04:21.476 --> 04:22.569
Shit.

04:22.645 --> 04:24.078
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
- No, it's...

04:24.147 --> 04:25.546
I really always liked her.

04:26.382 --> 04:28.577
Yeah, she... she really liked you, too.

04:28.651 --> 04:30.084
You actually...

04:30.153 --> 04:32.053
You actually made
quite the impression on her.

04:32.121 --> 04:34.988
She's... been kind of tough
on my boyfriends

04:35.091 --> 04:36.422
ever since we broke up.

04:36.492 --> 04:38.460
- Come on.
- No, really.

04:41.764 --> 04:42.992
Are you okay?

04:43.499 --> 04:44.966
What are you doing here?

04:48.104 --> 04:49.594
Well, my wife...

04:52.008 --> 04:53.600
[nervous chuckle]

04:53.676 --> 04:54.938
Amy, she...

04:55.011 --> 04:56.672
Oh, my God, I'm so sorry.

05:00.283 --> 05:01.841
Yeah, thank you.

05:05.822 --> 05:07.289
Thanks.

05:24.974 --> 05:26.464
What took you so long?

05:27.710 --> 05:29.439
Nothing. Everything was closed.

05:29.512 --> 05:30.501
[baby whines]

05:30.613 --> 05:31.602
- Sorry.
- It's all right.

05:31.681 --> 05:32.943
Isabelle, it's all right.

05:33.016 --> 05:34.608
Isabelle, look at me.

05:39.288 --> 05:40.619
It's okay.

05:40.690 --> 05:41.952
You're okay.

05:50.633 --> 05:50.700
[children screaming]

05:50.700 --> 05:52.531
[children screaming]

05:52.635 --> 05:55.570
[gunfire]

05:55.671 --> 05:58.367
[woman]
It's very difficult conditions of work,

05:58.474 --> 06:00.374
you have no infrastructure.

06:00.977 --> 06:04.640
When you get to places,
you just have to wait most of the time.

06:04.714 --> 06:06.705
[screaming continues]

06:06.816 --> 06:08.909
[gunfire continues]

06:11.387 --> 06:14.686
[man] Very often, we'd be
working together somewhere.

06:15.324 --> 06:18.487
You know, photographers everywhere.
Something would happen,

06:18.561 --> 06:20.756
they'd go to it like bees,

06:20.863 --> 06:23.024
looking at the same thing,
focus on the same thing.

06:25.201 --> 06:26.828
She'd get the shot.

06:38.214 --> 06:40.842
[man 2]...producing memorable images
under extreme hazards.

06:40.917 --> 06:42.248
Congratulations.

06:42.351 --> 06:45.582
[applause]

06:45.688 --> 06:49.784
[woman] When I first started, I thought
the job was to get as close as possible.

06:50.259 --> 06:54.195
The exciting part of it was probably
what drew me to it.

06:55.765 --> 06:59.758
Then I became confused
and I thought I had to stay

06:59.869 --> 07:03.771
until after the tanks had left
to show the damage, maybe,

07:03.873 --> 07:05.738
- The consequences, the toll of war.
- The consequences.

07:05.808 --> 07:06.797
[phone ringing]

07:06.909 --> 07:08.206
But, yes, the other side of the war.

07:08.277 --> 07:10.142
Yeah, I think that's most of
my photographs,

07:10.246 --> 07:13.215
my recent photographs
are the testimony of.

07:14.784 --> 07:16.274
[Charlie Rose]
How long will you do this?

07:16.385 --> 07:18.376
And when will you know it's time?

07:19.288 --> 07:20.755
I think it's...

07:21.724 --> 07:24.488
Yes, it's my responsibility.

07:25.795 --> 07:28.764
No, I don't think I should stop.
Why should I?

07:35.004 --> 07:36.596
[woman] In a twist of fate,

07:36.672 --> 07:39.937
having finally quit the hazardous world
of conflict photography,

07:40.009 --> 07:42.477
Isabelle Reed died in a car accident

07:42.578 --> 07:45.479
less than a mile from her home
in Nyack, New York.

07:45.581 --> 07:50.644
She was 57 years old,
leaving behind her husband and two sons.

08:00.596 --> 08:02.154
Well, you get the idea.

08:03.266 --> 08:04.858
It has to be this brief.

08:05.334 --> 08:08.997
People don't like to watch long films
as part of an exhibition.

08:09.105 --> 08:10.367
Sure, sure.

08:10.473 --> 08:13.442
Well, it seems...
it seems totally fine to me.

08:14.477 --> 08:17.708
Some of the prints of her photos
are already done.

08:17.813 --> 08:19.371
Did you see them on the way up?

08:19.482 --> 08:20.972
No, I didn't get a chance.

08:21.484 --> 08:23.179
- [woman 1] They look great.
- [woman 2] Yeah.

08:23.719 --> 08:25.983
- Good.
- [woman 1] We wanted to ask you--

08:26.055 --> 08:29.991
I know it's been a while, but have you
kept any of her material at your house,

08:30.059 --> 08:32.049
something we could take a look at?

08:32.160 --> 08:35.688
I'm afraid it's...
it's all a bit of a mess.

08:35.765 --> 08:38.393
Could there be something
from her last trip?

08:39.402 --> 08:42.371
The one to Syria.
I never saw any pictures from that.

08:42.438 --> 08:45.737
Well, I'll run it by Jonah and...

08:45.841 --> 08:48.810
Well... I don't see any reason
why you can't have a look.

08:48.878 --> 08:50.675
Great, we appreciate it.

09:03.025 --> 09:07.519
Did they tell you I'm doing an article
about Isabelle for the New York Times,

09:07.597 --> 09:10.361
- sort of a build up to the exhibition?
- Yeah, they told me.

09:12.768 --> 09:14.702
She always thought the one in print

09:14.770 --> 09:17.864
had been cropped a bit too much
on the right, down here.

09:18.674 --> 09:21.973
- Oh, yes.
- I see what she meant.

09:25.214 --> 09:27.341
So... when I write this article,

09:27.416 --> 09:31.409
I don't think I can avoid
mentioning how she died.

09:32.755 --> 09:34.450
That it wasn't really an accident.

09:37.793 --> 09:39.124
Yeah.

09:42.198 --> 09:46.532
So, are you saying that you
want to write that she killed herself?

09:46.602 --> 09:49.594
Gene, I don't want to be a part
of romanticizing what we do.

09:50.139 --> 09:51.902
Isabelle wouldn't either.

09:51.974 --> 09:56.070
I mean, this is hard.
It takes a toll, and...

09:57.213 --> 10:00.376
Well, I don't have to tell you,
but it was hard on her.

10:00.916 --> 10:02.110
Yeah.

10:03.452 --> 10:06.216
- Yeah.
- So... it's been a few years,

10:06.289 --> 10:09.952
so I just wanted you
and the boys to know before the...

10:10.059 --> 10:11.651
before the article comes out.

10:13.562 --> 10:15.757
And they know
what really happened, right?

10:17.066 --> 10:19.728
Well, Jonah obviously does, yeah.

10:20.436 --> 10:23.234
But Conrad-- Well, he was 1 2 so...

10:25.007 --> 10:26.497
That's a conversation.

10:29.845 --> 10:31.574
Here, let me show you something else.

10:46.996 --> 10:50.488
[woman speaking
distorted in background]

11:12.788 --> 11:14.619
[school bell rings]

12:15.451 --> 12:17.749
[phone rings]

12:24.393 --> 12:26.122
-Yeah?
-[Gene] Hey.

12:26.228 --> 12:28.458
- It's me.
- Yeah, I know, Dad.

12:30.966 --> 12:32.593
So what are you doing?

12:32.701 --> 12:35.568
I'm just with Kenneth and some others.

12:38.707 --> 12:39.969
Okay.

12:42.912 --> 12:45.574
No I just wondered what time
you were coming home?

12:45.648 --> 12:47.047
Don't know.

12:49.552 --> 12:50.780
I'm making tacos.

12:50.886 --> 12:53.753
Yeah, I'm kind of busy right now, Dad.
I'll talk to you later.

14:26.015 --> 14:29.917
♪♪ [rock music plays on radio]

14:30.019 --> 14:31.646
[door shuts]

14:32.354 --> 14:33.719
Hello?

14:39.728 --> 14:41.355
[door slams]

14:49.171 --> 14:50.570
Can I come in?

14:56.845 --> 14:58.938
[video game noises]

15:06.255 --> 15:07.620
What are you playing?

15:27.276 --> 15:28.641
Are you the girl?

15:29.244 --> 15:31.542
- It's a sorceress.
- A what?

15:32.047 --> 15:34.948
- I play other characters, too.
- Yeah.

15:40.255 --> 15:42.780
You know that meeting
I had this morning?

15:42.891 --> 15:46.918
Well, Richard was there.
You remember Richard, don't you?

15:47.896 --> 15:52.230
Well, he's gonna be writing this
article, and it just reminded me

15:52.301 --> 15:57.603
that there was some stuff that you
and I, we just needed to talk about.

16:04.079 --> 16:05.740
Can you turn that off?

16:05.814 --> 16:07.805
Or you can just put it on pause?

16:11.854 --> 16:14.254
Conrad, can you...
can you please turn that off?

16:14.323 --> 16:15.517
Get out!

16:18.093 --> 16:19.424
Get the fuck out.

16:22.031 --> 16:23.965
Don't you speak to me like that.

16:27.970 --> 16:30.200
I'm just trying to talk to you.

16:36.812 --> 16:39.474
All right, stop this.
Stop this. Stop it.

16:42.151 --> 16:45.018
This isn't funny. Stop it!

16:59.868 --> 17:01.859
[door opens, shuts]

17:29.932 --> 17:32.594
[crickets chirping]

18:41.737 --> 18:43.102
Wake up.

18:52.781 --> 18:54.942
[students chatter]

19:00.489 --> 19:05.859
"But now as he sink further and further
from the waves above,

19:05.961 --> 19:10.261
it wasn't the crucial moments
that came to him.

19:11.300 --> 19:14.792
Instead his thoughts traveled
to the outer reaches

19:14.870 --> 19:18.362
of his memory,
small events long forgotten.

19:19.975 --> 19:22.034
He remembered a sentence he had read

19:22.144 --> 19:26.376
in the paper a few days ago
and didn't understand.

19:27.316 --> 19:30.615
He thought of an old suitcase

19:30.686 --> 19:34.019
he had stored in his uncle's attic,

19:34.122 --> 19:37.285
a brief glance from a stranger,

19:37.359 --> 19:41.796
inconsensual fragments of presence--"

19:41.864 --> 19:43.491
Inconsequential.

19:45.534 --> 19:47.024
Inconsequential.

19:49.238 --> 19:51.570
"Inconsequential fragments

19:51.673 --> 19:54.733
all present at once
during his final seconds.

19:56.879 --> 19:59.347
Seconds that were not seconds anymore,

19:59.414 --> 20:02.247
but stretched out to minutes.

20:04.820 --> 20:06.344
Time suspended."

20:27.743 --> 20:30.109
"Seconds that were not seconds anymore,

20:30.212 --> 20:32.442
but stretched out to minutes.

20:35.017 --> 20:36.678
Time suspended. "

20:40.722 --> 20:42.952
What could she have been thinking?

20:43.058 --> 20:47.222
What went through her mind when she
realized the accident was unavoidable?

20:53.602 --> 20:57.561
She remembered lying on the beach,
dozing off,

20:57.639 --> 21:01.234
feeling the wind blowing
grains of sand on her face,

21:01.310 --> 21:04.711
thinking that if she just kept
still long enough,

21:04.780 --> 21:06.771
it would end up covering her.

21:12.654 --> 21:15.452
Maybe she remembered places.

21:16.058 --> 21:17.821
Our house.

21:19.461 --> 21:21.122
The hallway.

21:23.765 --> 21:25.426
The living room.

21:27.336 --> 21:29.804
Maybe she even thought about him.

21:30.639 --> 21:32.402
She could have.

21:33.108 --> 21:35.008
Some little thing.

21:35.677 --> 21:39.408
Something he himself had forgotten.

21:41.149 --> 21:43.447
- Conrad!
- He was hiding.

21:44.186 --> 21:47.519
- Listening to her calling out his name.
- Where are you?

21:49.157 --> 21:52.957
He realized now she must have seen him,

21:53.028 --> 21:55.997
all the time he was standing there.

21:56.098 --> 21:59.465
She just pretended not to,

21:59.534 --> 22:01.468
never straying too far away,

22:01.536 --> 22:05.666
always watching him
from the corner of her eye.

22:18.887 --> 22:20.445
[teacher] Conrad?

22:21.490 --> 22:22.684
Conrad.

22:24.526 --> 22:25.857
Conrad.

22:28.997 --> 22:31.158
She seems to be implying

22:31.233 --> 22:35.294
that the belief that
wisdom comes with old age is a myth.

22:36.738 --> 22:38.330
Wouldn't you agree?

22:53.989 --> 22:55.820
[cell phone buzzes]

23:02.197 --> 23:03.391
- Yeah?
- [Gene] Hey.

23:04.332 --> 23:06.357
- It's me.
- Yeah, I know, Dad.

23:09.404 --> 23:10.701
So what are you doing?

23:10.772 --> 23:13.570
I'm with Kenneth and some others.

23:13.675 --> 23:15.040
Okay.

23:18.346 --> 23:20.780
No, I just wondered what time
you were coming home?

23:20.882 --> 23:22.179
Don't know.

23:22.951 --> 23:25.078
[girls chattering]

23:25.187 --> 23:26.779
- I'm making tacos.
- Yeah.

23:26.888 --> 23:29.721
I'm kinda busy right now, Dad.
I'll talk to you later.

23:57.285 --> 24:00.118
[wind rustles]

24:07.429 --> 24:10.296
♪♪ [cafe music]

24:16.571 --> 24:18.232
How about just a coffee.

24:19.574 --> 24:20.939
Thank you so much.

24:31.353 --> 24:32.581
[barista] Can I help you?

25:11.459 --> 25:14.394
[Isabelle] And I was amazed because
I couldn't feel anything.

25:20.001 --> 25:21.969
But it was like...

25:26.541 --> 25:28.008
I felt like I was...

25:29.411 --> 25:30.901
...outside of it.

25:38.186 --> 25:42.520
All I could think was
this will destroy me,

25:42.591 --> 25:44.491
my life will never be the same.

25:46.094 --> 25:48.654
You make it sound like
that might be a good thing.

25:56.871 --> 25:58.498
[Isabelle]
And you were there, too.

25:58.573 --> 26:01.406
- [Gene] Really?
- [Isabelle] Yeah, just watching.

26:02.010 --> 26:03.341
[Gene] Just watching.

26:04.713 --> 26:07.341
[Isabelle] I couldn't see you,
but I could smell your cigarette.

26:07.415 --> 26:08.746
[Gene] My cigarette?

26:11.453 --> 26:13.887
In my dream, you are a smoker.

26:13.955 --> 26:15.388
[chuckles]

26:15.457 --> 26:18.790
So, why are you telling me this?

26:21.296 --> 26:23.526
I'm just wondering what it means, but...

26:26.701 --> 26:28.191
But it's only a dream.

26:28.270 --> 26:29.965
You want me to tell you what it means?

26:30.438 --> 26:31.598
Okay.

26:31.706 --> 26:36.200
You think I'm passive and boring,
or something like that.

26:37.078 --> 26:40.241
But really, you're bored because
you're hanging around the house all day.

26:41.283 --> 26:42.875
And you want to pick a fight with me.

26:44.653 --> 26:45.881
Interesting.

26:46.488 --> 26:47.819
Did I touch a nerve?

26:47.922 --> 26:50.618
Yeah, it did touch a nerve,
if you don't mind me saying so.

26:50.725 --> 26:52.317
This guy who's...

26:54.596 --> 26:57.258
...sitting there,
not saying anything, just watching...

26:57.332 --> 26:58.924
But you were not doing...

26:59.734 --> 27:01.167
No, you were just...

27:02.003 --> 27:04.403
Was it like... Was it like this?

27:08.576 --> 27:09.975
Or like this?

27:15.450 --> 27:16.644
Or like this...

27:19.754 --> 27:21.984
I don't know, but it was very scary.

27:22.090 --> 27:23.250
Really?

27:28.196 --> 27:29.595
[door shuts]

27:38.273 --> 27:40.833
♪♪ [upbeat music plays]

27:45.480 --> 27:46.777
Are you sleeping in?

27:49.517 --> 27:51.178
- Great to see you.
- Hi.

27:52.287 --> 27:55.882
- Good to see you too.
- So... where's Amy and the baby?

27:55.990 --> 27:57.855
Yeah, we finally decided against it.

27:58.393 --> 28:00.725
It's a six hour drive
with a baby in the car...

28:02.497 --> 28:04.658
- Yeah, I understand.
- Yeah.

28:04.733 --> 28:06.564
Sure. Okay, well...

28:06.668 --> 28:08.829
Let me get dressed and I'll see you
in a moment, okay?

28:08.903 --> 28:10.234
Sure, take your time.

28:16.044 --> 28:17.534
You want a cup of coffee?

28:27.389 --> 28:29.323
[Jonah]
Dad lets you eat that stuff?

28:29.858 --> 28:31.189
Yeah.

28:31.259 --> 28:32.692
That's interesting.

28:41.035 --> 28:43.003
Whoops!

28:50.078 --> 28:52.842
You can see that I've started there.
They're just...

28:52.914 --> 28:56.111
- Yeah. Yeah.
- You know, put aside some junk.

28:57.352 --> 28:59.786
You know, we can let
the agency deal with this.

28:59.888 --> 29:01.913
We can't give this
to the gallery people.

29:03.358 --> 29:05.292
I want to go through everything first.

29:05.860 --> 29:08.055
Remember that tacky
photo book they made?

29:08.463 --> 29:11.762
Listen, Dad, Mom was so protective
of her stuff, okay?

29:12.367 --> 29:14.699
I wouldn't even know we'd be
giving them. Look at this.

29:16.638 --> 29:18.902
Yes, we wouldn't want this to fall
into the wrong hands, would we?

29:19.741 --> 29:21.936
What are you do--
What are you even looking at here?

29:22.043 --> 29:23.271
This is your head shot?

29:23.378 --> 29:25.869
People saw this and said,
"Yes, we would like him."

29:26.548 --> 29:28.243
What is that look on your face?

29:28.316 --> 29:29.749
You look like
you're about to murder somebody

29:29.818 --> 29:31.445
on this side of the photograph.

29:33.154 --> 29:34.587
Turn it over.

29:37.992 --> 29:40.722
She kept it because she thought it was a
really good photo of me.

29:43.765 --> 29:47.064
My agent thought my good looks would
hamper a serious acting career.

29:47.135 --> 29:49.433
Yeah, your career might be hampered?
You were too attractive?

29:49.504 --> 29:51.165
- That was your problem.
- Too attractive.

29:55.443 --> 29:57.001
Why don't we get some breakfast?

29:57.111 --> 29:58.578
No, I'm fine.

29:58.646 --> 30:00.671
I think I have a pretty good idea
about how to do this.

30:00.782 --> 30:03.342
Come on. You haven't
been here for a while. Let's...

30:03.451 --> 30:06.147
- Let's do it together.
- Actually I'd love to just get started.

30:07.689 --> 30:09.316
Okay, sure.

31:49.090 --> 31:50.751
[knocking]

31:53.695 --> 31:55.686
- How is everything?
- [Jonah] Fine.

31:55.763 --> 31:57.355
Did you find the towel?

31:57.432 --> 31:58.922
Yeah, the one that was on the bed.

31:59.033 --> 32:00.125
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

32:00.234 --> 32:03.567
I had my room all ready for you guys.

32:03.638 --> 32:04.969
Good.

32:06.574 --> 32:08.872
It's... It's really great
to have you here.

32:08.943 --> 32:10.934
- Thanks.
- I've been thinking, you know.

32:11.045 --> 32:14.208
I think it's time we told Conrad
what happened with Isabelle.

32:17.552 --> 32:18.780
Wait...

32:18.886 --> 32:20.820
Why... why now?

32:20.922 --> 32:22.412
