01:20:43.822 --> 01:20:45.255
They want you there.

01:20:46.124 --> 01:20:47.352
They love you.

01:20:47.959 --> 01:20:49.551
You can feel it.

01:20:50.629 --> 01:20:53.689
And you love them, too.
More than anything.

01:21:00.605 --> 01:21:03.199
But you still feel like
you're in the way.

01:21:06.778 --> 01:21:09.144
In the way of what they usually do.

01:21:11.216 --> 01:21:13.946
Again, you get the feeling
you are in the wrong place.

01:21:22.494 --> 01:21:24.655
It's not that they don't want you there.

01:21:25.263 --> 01:21:26.560
But...

01:21:27.866 --> 01:21:29.834
... they don't really need you.

01:22:36.935 --> 01:22:39.199
[students chatter]

01:22:46.444 --> 01:22:47.638
[Gene] Hello?

01:22:51.650 --> 01:22:52.912
Hey.

01:22:56.554 --> 01:22:57.612
You okay?

01:23:05.630 --> 01:23:08.030
[Jonah] I thought you said it wouldn't
come out till the end of the month.

01:23:16.608 --> 01:23:18.075
It's a really big piece.

01:23:22.047 --> 01:23:25.380
He puts it into context,
just like you said he would.

01:23:28.853 --> 01:23:31.549
And he seems to know her really well.

01:23:33.558 --> 01:23:35.025
Is that what you wanted?

01:23:38.530 --> 01:23:39.861
Did Conrad see this?

01:23:42.133 --> 01:23:43.862
I don't know. I haven't seen him.

01:23:48.306 --> 01:23:51.002
Hi, this is Conrad.
Please leave a message after the tone.

01:23:51.342 --> 01:23:52.832
[Gene] Conrad, it's me.

01:23:53.378 --> 01:23:56.176
It's kind of important.
I... need to talk to you.

01:23:57.482 --> 01:23:58.710
Thanks.

01:24:30.615 --> 01:24:31.877
Conrad?

01:24:34.385 --> 01:24:35.613
Jonah?

01:24:44.696 --> 01:24:47.563
[teacher] You've reached Hannah Brennan.
Please leave a message.

01:25:06.417 --> 01:25:08.248
I think we gotta bring something,
you know?

01:25:08.319 --> 01:25:10.480
We cannot, like,
not bring something, right?

01:25:11.456 --> 01:25:13.117
I guess, yeah.

01:25:14.659 --> 01:25:16.786
- Are you sure you don't want anything?
- No, I'm okay.

01:25:55.500 --> 01:26:00.267
Is there any way if I, like,
pay double or something,

01:26:00.338 --> 01:26:03.830
that I could... maybe buy some beer?

01:26:31.236 --> 01:26:32.635
I think it's this way.

01:26:46.517 --> 01:26:48.485
♪♪ [music blaring]

01:26:50.889 --> 01:26:52.186
This should be it.

01:26:59.530 --> 01:27:00.690
Is that T.J.?

01:27:05.336 --> 01:27:06.860
Do we really want to do this?

01:27:09.073 --> 01:27:10.370
I don't know.

01:27:10.775 --> 01:27:12.003
We're here.

01:27:15.246 --> 01:27:16.838
I think I'm gonna go.

01:27:22.921 --> 01:27:24.115
Are you coming?

01:27:28.192 --> 01:27:29.420
I'm sorry.

01:27:31.896 --> 01:27:33.591
[chattering]

01:28:33.591 --> 01:28:36.321
[horn honking]
[tires screeching]

01:28:56.614 --> 01:28:58.343
♪♪ [music blaring]

01:28:58.449 --> 01:29:00.314
[phone ringing]

01:29:32.250 --> 01:29:34.343
[soft chuckle]

01:29:34.419 --> 01:29:35.681
You...

01:29:37.522 --> 01:29:41.356
You, like,
spat Miss Brennan in the face.

01:29:41.426 --> 01:29:43.360
[laughing]

01:29:50.568 --> 01:29:52.399
I have to get home.

01:29:57.075 --> 01:29:59.373
I don't feel so good.

01:30:08.953 --> 01:30:11.615
I'm, like, injured. I shouldn't be out.

01:30:13.291 --> 01:30:15.054
You know, but I just...

01:30:15.560 --> 01:30:19.462
You know, I never, like...
fall like that.

01:30:21.132 --> 01:30:23.794
Mia has my place now.

01:30:26.104 --> 01:30:30.200
She's... she's, like, really good,
you know.

01:30:34.479 --> 01:30:36.276
Did you read the...

01:30:38.282 --> 01:30:40.443
Did you look at that thing I gave you?

01:30:47.291 --> 01:30:50.055
You wrote that?
That was...

01:30:50.595 --> 01:30:52.119
You're Conrad?

01:30:54.665 --> 01:30:55.791
Yeah.

01:30:59.904 --> 01:31:02.964
Where... did you get all that stuff?

01:31:03.774 --> 01:31:05.105
What do you mean?

01:31:07.345 --> 01:31:09.677
Did you, like,
find it online or something?

01:31:10.481 --> 01:31:13.006
- No.
- You came up with all that?

01:31:14.785 --> 01:31:16.252
You know, I've...

01:31:20.758 --> 01:31:21.986
Are you okay?

01:31:23.828 --> 01:31:25.125
Oh, my God.

01:31:28.633 --> 01:31:30.191
[gags]

01:31:57.195 --> 01:31:58.560
Can you help me?

01:32:02.033 --> 01:32:04.058
Can you help me with the buttons?

01:32:42.873 --> 01:32:44.932
Tell me if anyone comes.

01:32:46.043 --> 01:32:47.510
And no peeking!

01:32:49.714 --> 01:32:51.773
Just a little peeking.

01:32:52.883 --> 01:32:55.044
[chuckles]

01:33:00.758 --> 01:33:02.055
You're peeking.

01:33:04.462 --> 01:33:06.794
[peeing]

01:34:07.458 --> 01:34:09.426
You're nice, you know that?

01:34:38.155 --> 01:34:43.024
He could still, many years from now,
recall the scene in all its detail.

01:34:44.562 --> 01:34:48.328
The lock of hair she carefully placed
behind her ear.

01:34:48.399 --> 01:34:51.891
The way the washing labels stuck out
from the neck of her tank top.

01:34:53.304 --> 01:34:57.536
The street lights that went out as they
passed Kevin Anderson's house.

01:34:59.844 --> 01:35:04.008
That strangely familiar smell of damp
earth he couldn't quite place.

01:35:07.351 --> 01:35:09.319
As a stranger passed,

01:35:09.387 --> 01:35:11.617
he glanced at them as he went by,

01:35:11.722 --> 01:35:13.849
probably thinking they were a couple.

01:35:15.259 --> 01:35:19.525
She had said that she wanted to have
lunch with him Tuesday after English.

01:35:19.597 --> 01:35:22.225
He knew that this would never happen.

01:35:23.033 --> 01:35:26.161
That she would feel differently
Monday back in school.

01:35:27.004 --> 01:35:32.374
But at that moment, he just enjoyed
that she felt like saying this to him.

01:35:33.444 --> 01:35:37.881
That she maybe really felt
like having lunch with him.

01:35:38.716 --> 01:35:42.413
That, while they were
walking there like that,

01:35:42.520 --> 01:35:44.681
having lunch together at school

01:35:44.755 --> 01:35:48.589
seemed to her like
a perfectly natural thing to do.

01:35:54.031 --> 01:35:55.396
Okay.

01:35:55.766 --> 01:35:57.097
Goodnight.

01:36:56.994 --> 01:36:59.462
[line ringing]

01:37:06.704 --> 01:37:09.195
[Gene] Where are you?
You okay?

01:37:26.190 --> 01:37:27.487
So it's true?

01:37:28.993 --> 01:37:30.358
The paper? It's true?

01:37:31.896 --> 01:37:33.158
Yes, it is.

01:37:40.204 --> 01:37:41.569
Why didn't you tell me?

01:37:45.976 --> 01:37:47.671
I saw her, you know.

01:37:49.713 --> 01:37:51.146
I saw how she was.

01:37:52.316 --> 01:37:53.544
I was here.

01:37:54.218 --> 01:37:55.412
I know.

01:37:56.253 --> 01:37:57.515
I'm sorry.

01:38:01.859 --> 01:38:04.851
Am I really that difficult to talk to?

01:38:04.929 --> 01:38:06.897
No, it's me.

01:38:07.698 --> 01:38:09.029
It's me, too.

01:38:09.567 --> 01:38:11.057
It's difficult.

01:38:26.684 --> 01:38:28.083
Hey...

01:38:34.725 --> 01:38:36.022
I'm okay.

01:38:36.860 --> 01:38:38.122
I know you are.

01:39:00.618 --> 01:39:02.051
I'm okay.

01:39:05.956 --> 01:39:08.481
You're sure you don't want something,
some breakfast, maybe?

01:39:08.592 --> 01:39:10.719
[Conrad]
No, I've gotta get some sleep.

01:39:10.794 --> 01:39:12.989
You shouldn't stay out like that,
you know?

01:39:13.097 --> 01:39:14.428
I know.

01:39:14.498 --> 01:39:16.966
You know, Jonah...

01:39:18.435 --> 01:39:20.096
He's not doing so well.

01:39:23.774 --> 01:39:25.002
Yeah.

01:39:25.843 --> 01:39:27.140
Yeah, I know.

01:39:28.312 --> 01:39:30.280
I'll talk to him. You get some sleep.

01:39:43.293 --> 01:39:45.193
- Hi.
- So how you doing?

01:39:48.265 --> 01:39:49.857
It's time to go home to Amy.

01:39:52.536 --> 01:39:53.867
Yeah.

01:39:55.673 --> 01:39:56.970
Yeah, I know.

01:40:00.344 --> 01:40:03.279
I don't think I can drive right now.
I've been drinking.

01:40:03.347 --> 01:40:05.679
Come on, I'll take you.

01:40:46.423 --> 01:40:48.857
[Conrad]
Mom had been away like she used to,

01:40:48.926 --> 01:40:53.386
in Africa or something,
and she came back for her exhibition.

01:40:55.332 --> 01:40:57.323
But she had a baby with her.

01:40:58.035 --> 01:41:00.731
And when I was little,
I thought she should do that.

01:41:01.772 --> 01:41:03.330
Just bring them back here.

01:41:06.577 --> 01:41:08.204
But this was Jonah's baby.

01:41:09.379 --> 01:41:13.247
And me and Dad were very curious
because we hadn't really met her.

01:41:14.017 --> 01:41:15.609
Not for real.

01:41:15.919 --> 01:41:18.285
The baby was a very old man.

01:41:18.889 --> 01:41:22.017
And it didn't feel strange.
It was just Jonah's baby.

01:41:23.260 --> 01:41:25.228
He couldn't really talk,
being a baby and all,

01:41:25.295 --> 01:41:28.856
but he was very nice
and he really liked me.

01:41:29.633 --> 01:41:30.759
I could tell.

01:41:31.802 --> 01:41:34.430
I can remember
we all felt proud, you know...

01:41:35.572 --> 01:41:37.802
... that she was our mother.

